==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reverberation
<hw>Re*ver`ber*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧verb⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of
reverberating; especially, the act of reflecting light or heat, or
reechoing sound; <as>as, the <ex>reverberation</ex> of rays from a
mirror; the <ex>reverberation</ex> of rays from a mirror; the
<ex>reverberation</ex> of voices; the <ex>reverberation</ex> of heat or
flame in a furnace.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reverberative</ent>⟦br⟧
